   <text>
      <body>
         <div>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-1a.1" xml:lang="en">In general although men possess (inborn) nature, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-1a.2" xml:lang="en">their hearts do not have fixed intentions, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-1a.3" xml:lang="en">they depend on (external) objects </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-1a.4" xml:lang="en">and only then arise, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-1a.5" xml:lang="en">they depend on pleasure/preference </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-1a.6" xml:lang="en">and only then act, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-1a.7" xml:lang="en">they depend on (repeated) practice </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-1a.8" xml:lang="en">and only then become fixed. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-2a.1" xml:lang="en">The vital forces of joy, anger, sorrow and sadness, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-2a.2" xml:lang="en">are inborn nature. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-2a.3" xml:lang="en">As it comes to their being manifested on the outside, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-2a.4" xml:lang="en">then it is because external objects bring it about. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-2a.5" xml:lang="en">[Nature] comes from the decree, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-2a.6" xml:lang="en">and the decree is sent down from Heaven. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-2a.7" xml:lang="en">The way begins with the emotions, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-2a.8" xml:lang="en">and the emotions arise from inborn nature. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-2a.9" xml:lang="en">At the beginning it is close to the emotions, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-2a.10" xml:lang="en">at the end it is close to righteousness. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-3a.1" xml:lang="en">Those who understand emotions are able to externalize them, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-3a.2" xml:lang="en">those who understand righteousness are able to internalize [it. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-3a.3" xml:lang="en">To like and to dislike, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-3a.4" xml:lang="en">is due to inborn nature. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-3a.5" xml:lang="en">What] we like and dislike, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-3a.6" xml:lang="en">are external objects. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-3a.7" xml:lang="en">Deeming things good </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-3a.8" xml:lang="en">or not good, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-3a.9" xml:lang="en">is due to inborn nature, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-3a.10" xml:lang="en">what we deem good </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-3a.11" xml:lang="en">or not good, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-3a.12" xml:lang="en">is due to circumstances. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-4a.1" xml:lang="en">In general, inborn nature is the main element, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-4a.2" xml:lang="en">external objects (just) bring it out. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-4a.3" xml:lang="en">Metal and stone possess (the ability to) sound, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-4a.4" xml:lang="en">but if you do not beat them, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-4a.5" xml:lang="en">they do not give a sound. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-4a.6" xml:lang="en">[Even though people has inborn nature, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-4a.7" xml:lang="en">if the heart does not bring it about </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-4a.8" xml:lang="en">it is not externalized.] </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-5a.1" xml:lang="en">In general even if the heart has intentions, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-5a.2" xml:lang="en">if they are not shared (with others) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-5a.3" xml:lang="en">they cannot [be acted upon]. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-5a.4" xml:lang="en">[Man cannot act] alone, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-5a.5" xml:lang="en">just as the mouth cannot speak alone. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-5a.6" xml:lang="en">Oxen are born and then grow (robust), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-5a.7" xml:lang="en">wild geese are born and then stretch (their long neck), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-5a.8" xml:lang="en">their inborn nature [makes them like this]. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-5a.9" xml:lang="en">(but) [men] by studying </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-5a.10" xml:lang="en">sometimes can cause it (to be different). </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-6a.1" xml:lang="en">[In general for things there is none that is not different (=they are all different from each other depending on their inborn nature). </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-6a.2" xml:lang="en">The propping up of hard (objects), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-6a.3" xml:lang="en">it is their hardness that brings it about; </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-6a.4" xml:lang="en">the binding (together) of soft (objects), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-6a.5" xml:lang="en">it is their softness that brings it about. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-6a.6" xml:lang="en">As for (every man) within the four seas], their inborn nature is the same. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-6a.7" xml:lang="en">That in using their minds each is different, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-6a.8" xml:lang="en">it is education that makes it like this. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-7a.1" xml:lang="en">In general, as for (human) inborn nature, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-7a.2" xml:lang="en">some (things) move it, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-7a.3" xml:lang="en">some entice it, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-7a.4" xml:lang="en">some restrains it, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-7a.5" xml:lang="en">some polish it, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-7a.6" xml:lang="en">some bring [it out, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-7a.7" xml:lang="en">some nurture it], </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-7a.8" xml:lang="en">some let it grow. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-8a.1" xml:lang="en">In general, what moves inborn nature, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-8a.2" xml:lang="en">are external objects, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-8a.3" xml:lang="en">what entices inborn nature, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-8a.4" xml:lang="en">is pleasure, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-8a.5" xml:lang="en">what restrains inborn nature, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-8a.6" xml:lang="en">is intention, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-8a.7" xml:lang="en">what polishes inborn nature, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-8a.8" xml:lang="en">is righteousness, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-8a.9" xml:lang="en">what brings out inborn nature, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-8a.10" xml:lang="en">is circumstance, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-8a.11" xml:lang="en">what nurtures inborn nature, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-8a.12" xml:lang="en">is practice, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-8a.13" xml:lang="en">what causes inborn nature to grow, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-8a.14" xml:lang="en">is the way. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-9a.1" xml:lang="en">In general what is seen is called an external object, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-9a.2" xml:lang="en">what brings happiness to oneself, I call pleasure, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-9a.3" xml:lang="en">the disposition of things, I call circumstances; </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-9a.4" xml:lang="en">having (intentional) activities, I call intent. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-9a.5" xml:lang="en">Righteousness </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-9a.6" xml:lang="en">is the mark of distinction of the myriad good (things). </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-9a.7" xml:lang="en">practice, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-9a.8" xml:lang="en">is having the means to exercise one’s inborn nature. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-9a.9" xml:lang="en">The way </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-9a.10" xml:lang="en">[is the way of the myriad things.] </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-10a.1" xml:lang="en">In general for the way, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-10a.2" xml:lang="en">the main thing is the technique of the heart. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-10a.3" xml:lang="en">The way consists of four techniques, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-10a.4" xml:lang="en">only the human way </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-10a.5" xml:lang="en">can be followed as a way. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-10a.6" xml:lang="en">As for the other three techniques, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-10a.7" xml:lang="en">they can be talked about and that’s all. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-11a.1" xml:lang="en">As for the poems, documents, rites and music, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-11a.2" xml:lang="en">their first expression was in every case generated among [men. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-11a.3" xml:lang="en">As for the poems, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-11a.4" xml:lang="en">there were] activities </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-11a.5" xml:lang="en">and they chanted about them. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-11a.6" xml:lang="en">As for the documents, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-11a.7" xml:lang="en">there were activities </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-11a.8" xml:lang="en">and they spoke of them. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-11a.9" xml:lang="en">As for the rites and music, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-11a.10" xml:lang="en">there were activities </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-11a.11" xml:lang="en">and they enacted them. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-12a.1" xml:lang="en">The sage (=Confucius) compared their categories </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-12a.2" xml:lang="en">and chose them and assembled them, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-12a.3" xml:lang="en">he analyzed their sequence </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-12a.4" xml:lang="en">and went against and according to them (=ordered them), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-12a.5" xml:lang="en">embodied their propriety </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-12a.6" xml:lang="en">and restrained them and adorned them, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-12a.7" xml:lang="en">gave a pattern to their emotions </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-12a.8" xml:lang="en">and externalized them (as well as) internalize them, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-12a.9" xml:lang="en">and then he brought them back to education. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-13a.1" xml:lang="en">Education </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-13a.2" xml:lang="en">is the means by which one generates virtue in the innermost feelings. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-13a.3" xml:lang="en">The rites </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-13a.4" xml:lang="en">[arise from the emotions, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-13a.5" xml:lang="en">and sometimes] (the rites) stir them (=the emotions); </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-13a.6" xml:lang="en">according to the (different) affairs </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-13a.7" xml:lang="en">and following the (different) methods </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-13a.8" xml:lang="en">one should regulate them. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-13a.9" xml:lang="en">The order of their sequence (of the emotions) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-13a.10" xml:lang="en">is the way of righteousness. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-14a.1" xml:lang="en">To have an order </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-14a.2" xml:lang="en">and give them (=the emotions) restraint </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-14a.3" xml:lang="en">is being well patterned. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-14a.4" xml:lang="en">[To bring forward a countenanced] appearance </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-14a.5" xml:lang="en">and thereby adorn them (=the emotions), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-14a.6" xml:lang="en">is restraint. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-14a.7" xml:lang="en">The gentleman beautifies his emotions, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-14a.8" xml:lang="en">ennobles his righteousness, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-14a.9" xml:lang="en">perfects his restraint, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-14a.10" xml:lang="en">makes lovable his appearance, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-14a.11" xml:lang="en">makes enjoyable his way </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-14a.12" xml:lang="en">and pleasurable his teachings, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-14a.13" xml:lang="en">and thereby shows respect. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-15a.1" xml:lang="en">Bowing ritually, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-15a.2" xml:lang="en">[is the way to express submission. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-15a.3" xml:lang="en">Appropriate etiquette, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-15a.4" xml:lang="en">(shows one) to be well patterned.] </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-15a.5" xml:lang="en">Offerings of silk, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-15a.6" xml:lang="en">are the means to enact trust and reliability; </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-15a.7" xml:lang="en">their gift </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-15a.8" xml:lang="en">is (an instance of) the way of righteousness. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-16a.1" xml:lang="en">Laughter, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-16a.2" xml:lang="en">is (a sign of the) superficial moisture (=initial influence) [shallow abundance CH] of delight. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-16a.3" xml:lang="en">Joy, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-16a.4" xml:lang="en">[is (a sign of the) deep moisture (=lasting influence)] [deep abundance CH] of delight. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-16a.5" xml:lang="en">[In general], as for sounds, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-16a.6" xml:lang="en">when their externalization in the emotions </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-16a.7" xml:lang="en">is sincere, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-16a.8" xml:lang="en">then their (way of) entering and agitating (=taking hold of) the man’s heart </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-16a.9" xml:lang="en">is deep. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-17a.1" xml:lang="en">Hearing the sound of laughter, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-17a.2" xml:lang="en">how fresh </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-17a.3" xml:lang="en">is that happiness. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-17a.4" xml:lang="en">When you hear singing and chanting, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-17a.5" xml:lang="en">[how joyous </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-17a.6" xml:lang="en">is that excitement]. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-17a.7" xml:lang="en">When you hear the sounds of the lute and zither, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-17a.8" xml:lang="en">how agitated </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-17a.9" xml:lang="en">are these sighs. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-18a.1" xml:lang="en">When one watches the Lai and Wu dances, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-18a.2" xml:lang="en">how reverent </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-18a.3" xml:lang="en">are these performances. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-18a.4" xml:lang="en">When one watches the Shao and Xia dances, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-18a.5" xml:lang="en">[how vigorous </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-18a.6" xml:lang="en">is their moderation.] </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-18a.7" xml:lang="en">When one intones his concerns </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-18a.8" xml:lang="en">(this) thereby moves one’s heart, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-18a.9" xml:lang="en">like a (deep) sigh. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-19a.1" xml:lang="en">If their standing in the rhythm (=dancing) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-19a.2" xml:lang="en">is long </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-19a.3" xml:lang="en">If in their reverting to goodness </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-19a.4" xml:lang="en">and returning to the beginning, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-19a.5" xml:lang="en">(they) are careful </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-19a.6" xml:lang="en">if their externalizations and their internalizations </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-19a.7" xml:lang="en">are smooth， </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-19a.8" xml:lang="en">(this means that) they control its virtue (=the virtue of music). </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-19a.9" xml:lang="en">[As for the music of Zheng and Wei, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-19a.10" xml:lang="en">even if it is not the correct] sound (=music), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-19a.11" xml:lang="en">(people) follow it. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-20a.1" xml:lang="en">In general ancient music stirs the heart, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-20a.2" xml:lang="en">while excessive [music stirs intentions (=desires), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-20a.3" xml:lang="en">in all cases they are things that transform] the people. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-20a.4" xml:lang="en">The Lai and Wu (music) rejoices in (King Wu) obtaining (the empire), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-20a.5" xml:lang="en">the Shao and Xia (music) rejoices in (Shun’s beautiful) emotions. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-21a.1" xml:lang="en">In general [extreme joy/music] necessarily (results in) grief, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-21a.2" xml:lang="en">wailing also is (one expression of) sorrow, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-21a.3" xml:lang="en">in all cases they bring emotions to the outmost. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-21a.4" xml:lang="en">Sorrow and joy/music, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-21a.5" xml:lang="en">their nature is close to each other, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-21a.6" xml:lang="en">therefore their (outcome in the) heart is not far. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-22a.1" xml:lang="en">The motions of the heart due to wailing, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-22a.2" xml:lang="en">gradually turn to grief, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-22a.3" xml:lang="en">their intensity has such a deep longing, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-22a.4" xml:lang="en">and they end in a feeling of grief. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-22a.5" xml:lang="en">The motions of the heart due to joy/music </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-22a.6" xml:lang="en">are so very deep and sad and anxious, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-22a.7" xml:lang="en">their intensity </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-22a.8" xml:lang="en">is so unrestrained </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-22a.9" xml:lang="en">and sad, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-22a.10" xml:lang="en">pensive </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-22a.11" xml:lang="en">and thoughtful. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-23a.1" xml:lang="en">In general there are sorrowful thoughts </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-23a.2" xml:lang="en">and then there is sadness, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-23a.3" xml:lang="en">[in general] there are joyous thoughts </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-23a.4" xml:lang="en">and then there is delight. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-23a.5" xml:lang="en">In general the operations of the mind while thinking </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-23a.6" xml:lang="en">are (very) intense. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-24a.1" xml:lang="en">Sighing, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-24a.2" xml:lang="en">is the way of (expressing) thoughts. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-24a.3" xml:lang="en">If its sound changes </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-24a.4" xml:lang="en">then [his heart follows it], </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-24a.5" xml:lang="en">if his heart changes, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-24a.6" xml:lang="en">then his sound is also like this (=changed in the same way). </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-25a.1" xml:lang="en">Moaning comes from sadness, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-25a.2" xml:lang="en">loud sounds] come from joy, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-25a.3" xml:lang="en">sadness comes from (sad) sounds, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-25a.4" xml:lang="en">happiness comes from the heart. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-26a.1" xml:lang="en">In general, others’ emotions (=a passionate behavior) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-26a.2" xml:lang="en">are likable. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-26a.3" xml:lang="en">If one uses (displays) the proper emotions, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-26a.4" xml:lang="en">even if one commits mistakes, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-26a.5" xml:lang="en">he is not disliked. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-26a.6" xml:lang="en">If one does not use (display) [the proper emotions], </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-26a.7" xml:lang="en">even if one (achieves aims) difficult (to obtain), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-26a.8" xml:lang="en">he is not held in esteem. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-27a.1" xml:lang="en">(The gentleman) has not yet spoken and he is trusted, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-27a.2" xml:lang="en">because he has beautiful emotions. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-27a.3" xml:lang="en">He has not yet transformed them by education and the people conform to the standards, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-27a.4" xml:lang="en">because his emotions are good. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-27a.5" xml:lang="en">[He has not yet given prizes and the people are encouraged, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-27a.6" xml:lang="en">because he holds blessings (=virtue). </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-27a.7" xml:lang="en">He has not yet administered punishments] and the people are in awe of him, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-27a.8" xml:lang="en">because he has majesty in the heart. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-28a.1" xml:lang="en">His status is low and people take him in high esteem, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-28a.2" xml:lang="en">because he has virtue, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-28a.3" xml:lang="en">he is poor and people congregate around him, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-28a.4" xml:lang="en">because he possesses the way. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-28a.5" xml:lang="en">If one is dwelling alone and still being joyous, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-28a.6" xml:lang="en">it is because he has entered (the stage) of ritual propriety. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-28a.7" xml:lang="en">If (even those who) dislike him </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-28a.8" xml:lang="en">still cannot find (anything) wrong (in his conduct), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-28a.9" xml:lang="en">it is because he has reached righteousness. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-28a.10" xml:lang="en">If they find (something) wrong (in his conduct) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-28a.11" xml:lang="en">and still cannot dislike him, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-28a.12" xml:lang="en">it is because he is sincere in his humanity. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-29a.1" xml:lang="en">If his conduct has no mistakes, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-29a.2" xml:lang="en">it is because he knows the way. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-29a.3" xml:lang="en">[When one hears about the way and reverts (=applies it) to those above, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-29a.4" xml:lang="en">this is connecting above. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-29a.5" xml:lang="en">When one hears about the way and reverts to those below, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-29a.6" xml:lang="en">this is connecting below]. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-29a.7" xml:lang="en">When one hears about the way and reverts to oneself, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-29a.8" xml:lang="en">this is to cultivate one’s person. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-30a.1" xml:lang="en">By connecting above one approaches the service of the lord, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-30a.2" xml:lang="en">by connecting below one obtains the masses and approaches the conduct of government, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-30a.3" xml:lang="en">by cultivating one’s person one comes closer to reach virtue. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-30a.4" xml:lang="en">Sharing the same methods and forming connections, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-30a.5" xml:lang="en">it is because of the way. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-30a.6" xml:lang="en">Not sharing the same methods but still forming connections, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-30a.7" xml:lang="en">it is because of some special reasons. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-31a.1" xml:lang="en">Sharing the same joy and forming connections, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-31a.2" xml:lang="en">it is because of virtue. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-31a.3" xml:lang="en">Not sharing the same joy and still forming connections, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-31a.4" xml:lang="en">it is because of calculations. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-31a.5" xml:lang="en">In dealing with (affairs) inside the doors (=the family), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-31a.6" xml:lang="en">you want (to keep them) discreet. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-31a.7" xml:lang="en">In dealing with (affairs) outside the doors (=public affairs), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-31a.8" xml:lang="en">you want (to keep them strictly) regulated. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-32a.1" xml:lang="en">In general, in your own person you should seek (just) to be tranquil and not excessive, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-32a.2" xml:lang="en"> </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-32a.3" xml:lang="en">in your thoughts you should seek to be deep and without violence, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-32a.4" xml:lang="en">in retreating you should be solemn and not careless; </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-32a.5" xml:lang="en">in advancing, you should be yielding and </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-32a.6" xml:lang="en"> </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-32a.7" xml:lang="en"> </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-33a.1" xml:lang="en">The gentleman in holding to his (original) intent </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-33a.2" xml:lang="en">necessarily has a truly magnificent heart, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-33a.3" xml:lang="en">in speaking </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-33a.4" xml:lang="en">he necessarily has a very magnanimous sincerity, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-33a.5" xml:lang="en">in the rituals of host and guest </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-33a.6" xml:lang="en">he necessarily has a very dignified demeanor, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-33a.7" xml:lang="en">in the rituals of offering sacrifices </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-33a.8" xml:lang="en">he necessarily has a very dignified respect, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-33a.9" xml:lang="en">in mourning </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-33a.10" xml:lang="en">he necessarily has a very deeply [felt grief]. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-34a.1" xml:lang="en">[In general to make] people happy </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-34a.2" xml:lang="en">you should not treat them with stinginess, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-34a.3" xml:lang="en">[you should] do things personally. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-34a.4" xml:lang="en">(For your) words to reach (their target) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-34a.5" xml:lang="en">you should clearly act upon them </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-34a.6" xml:lang="en">and not be false. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-35a.1" xml:lang="en">In general in social intercourse you should not be excessive, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-35a.2" xml:lang="en">you should make it to have (a beginning and) an end (=constant). </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-35a.3" xml:lang="en">In general on the road (=in public) you should not think (too much) (=be too self-conscious), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-35a.4" xml:lang="en">(but) you should not talk alone (=be too self-reliant) (either). </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-35a.5" xml:lang="en">When living alone (reaching independence in the world) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-35a.6" xml:lang="en">then you should practice what your father and elder brothers enjoy. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-35a.7" xml:lang="en">If there is no [great] damage, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-35a.8" xml:lang="en">it is acceptable to receive minor injustices, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-35a.9" xml:lang="en">and when they are finished you should not talk about them again. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-35a.10" xml:lang="en">In general in sad and calamitous affairs (big crisis) one (should) seek to take responsibility, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-35a.11" xml:lang="en">in joyous things one (should seek) to be last. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-36a.1" xml:lang="en">In general in studying </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-36a.2" xml:lang="en">If one seeks after one’s heart </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-36a.3" xml:lang="en">with deliberate action (falsity), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-36a.4" xml:lang="en">he will not obtain it. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-36a.5" xml:lang="en">That one cannot use deliberate action (falsity) (for obtaining control over it), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-36a.6" xml:lang="en">can be known. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-36a.7" xml:lang="en">If (one) makes mistakes in ten [actions (=many times), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-36a.8" xml:lang="en">his mind must be present in it (=this course of action); </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-36a.9" xml:lang="en">if one looks at his appearance, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-36a.10" xml:lang="en">how can one miss (to uncover) the (underlying) emotions? (i.e. one’s own emotions are apparent from one’s behavioral pattern)] </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-37a.1" xml:lang="en">Fairness, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-37a.2" xml:lang="en">is the method (=manifestation) of righteousness; </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-37a.3" xml:lang="en">righteousness </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-37a.4" xml:lang="en">is the manifestation of respect; </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-37a.5" xml:lang="en">respect, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-37a.6" xml:lang="en">is the regulation of things. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-37a.7" xml:lang="en">Sincerity </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-37a.8" xml:lang="en">is the manifestation of humanity; </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-37a.9" xml:lang="en">humanity </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-37a.10" xml:lang="en">is the manifestation of inborn nature. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-37a.11" xml:lang="en">Inborn nature in all likelihood begets it (humanity). </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-37a.12" xml:lang="en">[Loyalty </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-37a.13" xml:lang="en">is the manifestation of trust. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-37a.14" xml:lang="en">Trust </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-37a.15" xml:lang="en">is the manifestation of emotions]. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-38a.1" xml:lang="en">Emotions originate from inborn nature. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-38a.2" xml:lang="en">There are seven kinds of affections, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-38a.3" xml:lang="en">only the affection (coming from) the inborn nature </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-38a.4" xml:lang="en">comes close to humanity. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-38a.5" xml:lang="en">There are five kinds of wisdom, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-38a.6" xml:lang="en">only the dao (coming from) righteousness </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-38a.7" xml:lang="en">can come close to loyalty. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-38a.8" xml:lang="en">There are three kinds of dislikes, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-38a.9" xml:lang="en">only the dislike of inhumanity </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-38a.10" xml:lang="en">can [come close to righteousness. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-38a.11" xml:lang="en">There are four (ways) to follow, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-38a.12" xml:lang="en">but only the way of man] </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-38a.13" xml:lang="en">is such that it can be followed. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-39a.1" xml:lang="en">In general, among the distressing (=intense) (ways) of using the heart/mind, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-39a.2" xml:lang="en">thought is the most intense. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-39a.3" xml:lang="en">Among the (worse) troubles of using wisdom, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-39a.4" xml:lang="en">(the one deriving from) exhaustion is the most intense. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-39a.5" xml:lang="en">Among the extreme (ways) of using the emotions, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-39a.6" xml:lang="en">sadness and joy are the most intense. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-39a.7" xml:lang="en">Of the (kind of) comforts (deriving from) using the body, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-39a.8" xml:lang="en">pleasure is the most intense. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-39a.9" xml:lang="en">Of the (kind of aims for which) to use strength to the utmost, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-39a.10" xml:lang="en">profit is the most prominent. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-40a.1" xml:lang="en">The eye likes (beautiful) appearances, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-40a.2" xml:lang="en">the ear enjoys (beautiful) sounds, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-40a.3" xml:lang="en">(this is the origin of) the anxious (pent up) qi, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-40a.4" xml:lang="en">people easily die because of this. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-41a.1" xml:lang="en">If one’s behavior is restrained and regulated, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-41a.2" xml:lang="en">(but) one does not have a very moderate heart, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-41a.3" xml:lang="en">then it is (merely) an adornment (=hypocrisy). </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-41a.4" xml:lang="en">If one’s own behavior is very moderate, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-41a.5" xml:lang="en">(but) one does not have beginning to end (=thorough) intention, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-41a.6" xml:lang="en">then one is indolent. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-41a.7" xml:lang="en">If one’s talk is smart and his words are bright, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-41a.8" xml:lang="en">but one does not have a very inept (=simple) heart, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-41a.9" xml:lang="en">then he is drifting (=dissolute). </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-42a.1" xml:lang="en">If one can be joyfully approached (by others) in harmony and peace, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-42a.2" xml:lang="en">if he does not have some stirring and arousing emotions </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-42a.3" xml:lang="en">then it is shameful. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-42a.4" xml:lang="en">If one’s behavior is very joyous, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-42a.5" xml:lang="en">(but) one does not nourishes it, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-42a.6" xml:lang="en">it is not admissible. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-42a.7" xml:lang="en">If one’s behavior is very sincere, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-42a.8" xml:lang="en">(but) one does not help it (to grow), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0034_tls_001-42a.9" xml:lang="en">it is not enough. </seg>
                </p>

         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
